# Python bytecode + tool caches only. Everything else (reference/, tests/,
# gtests/, bench/, notes/, SUMMARY.md, PRODUCTION_PLAN.md, AGENTS.md, demo_plan.py,
# uv.lock, *.md reports) is intentionally NOT ignored — it stays untracked and
# visible in `git status` so we can decide per-item what belongs in the public repo.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.swp
.venv/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.benchmarks/
